  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Activation of the hypothalamus-pituitary-adrenal system is monitored using saliva cortisol
      sampling during the antidepressant treatment with amitriptyline and paroxetine in moderately
      to severely depressed patients. Additionally, serum and plasma are sampled during the 5-week
      study period in order to study endocrine and metabolic parameters.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
